  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Ellicott's Commentary for English Readers",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "THE SUM OF THE GOLD, SILVER, AND BRONZE EMPLOYED IN THE TABERNACLE.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(21) This is the sum.—Kalisch translates, “These are the accounts”; Canon Cook, “This is the reckoning.” The expression recurs in Numbers 26:63.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "(21) ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "This is the sum.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—Kalisch translates, “These are the accounts”; Canon Cook, “This is the reckoning.” The expression recurs in ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Numbers 26:63",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ".",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The tabernacle of testimony—i.e., the dwelling which was to contain God’s “testimony” against sin—the Ten Commandments.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "The tabernacle of testimony",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—i.e., the dwelling which was to contain God’s “testimony” against sin—the Ten Commandments.",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "For the service of the Levites.—Rather, a service of the Levites: i.e., a service which they rendered “by the hand,” or through the instrumentality of Ithamar. Ithamar was the youngest of the sons of Aaron (Exodus 6:23).",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "For the service of the Levites.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—Rather, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "a service of the Levites: i.e., ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "a service which they rendered “by the hand,” or through the instrumentality of Ithamar. Ithamar was the youngest of the sons of Aaron (",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
