  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verses 21-31.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - THE SUM OF THE TABERNACLE, OR WEIGHT OF THE METALS EMPLOYED IN IT. Before dismissing the subject of the construction of the tabernacle, Moses places on record the sum of the gold, silver and bronze contributed and consumed in the work. At the same time he informs us who was the accountant by whom the sum was made up (ver. 21), and what were the portions of the work formed of each metal (vers. 24, 27, 28, 30, 31). Incidentally he mentions the number of the congregation at this period (ver. 26), and the weight of the \"sockets\" or \"bases\" (ver. 27). ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 21.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "This is the sum",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Or \"numbering\" (as in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Numbers 26:63",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "The tabernacle of testimony",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The tabernacle, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "i.e.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", of which the great glory was that it contained \"the testimony\" or \"Two Tables.\" Compare ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 25:16",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "For the service of the Levites",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Literally \"a service of the Levites by the hand of Ithamar,\" etc. - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "i.e.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " \"a service which was performed by the Levites at the command of Ithamar.\" It is somewhat remarkable that the direction of the Levites should be assigned to Ithamar, rather than to Nadab or Abihu. Exodus 38:21",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Keil and Delitzsch Biblical Commentary on the Old Testament",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Estimate of the Amount of Metal Used. - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 38:21",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". \"These are the numbered things of the dwelling, of the dwelling of the testimony, that were numbered at the command of Moses, through the service of the Levites, by the hand of Ithamar, the son of Aaron the priest.\" פּקוּדים does not mean the numbering (equivalent to מפקד   ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Samuel 4:9",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", or פּקדּה ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 17:14",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 26:11",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), as Knobel supposes, but here as elsewhere, even in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Numbers 26:63-64",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", it signifies \"the numbered;\" the only difference being, that in most cases it refers to persons, here to things, and that the reckoning consisted not merely in the counting and entering of the different things, but in ascertaining their weight and estimating their worth. Lyra has given the following correct rendering of this heading: \"haec est summa numeri ponderis eorum, quae facta sunt in tabernaculo ex auro, argento et aere.\" It was apparently superfluous to enumerate the different articles again, as this had been repeatedly done before. The weight of the different metals, therefore, is all that is given. The \"dwelling\" is still further described as \"the dwelling of the testimony,\" because the testimony, i.e., the decalogue written with the finger of God upon the tables of stone, was kept in the dwelling, and this testimony formed the base of the throne of Jehovah, and was the material pledge that Jehovah would cause His name, His manifested presence, to dwell there, and would thus show Himself to His people in grace and righteousness. \"That which was numbered\" is an explanatory apposition to the previous clause, \"the numbering of the dwelling;\" and the words הלויּם עבדת, which follow, are an accusative construed freely to indicate more particularly the mode of numbering (Ewald, 204 a), viz., \"through the service,\" or \"by means of the service of the Levites,\" not for their service. \"By the hand of Ithamar:\" who presided over the calculations which the Levites carried out under his superintendence.",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  }
